## 📊 3. Vulnerability Management (Issue Tracking)

One of the major differentiators of these pipelines is the active generation of reports. Instead of forcing the developer to read the GitHub Actions logs to understand the flaws, the libraries extract JSON reports (Trivy, Gosec, Bandit, OWASP) and convert them into Markdown format.

These reports use the `JasonEtco/create-an-issue` *Action* to automatically open, update, and centralize vulnerabilities and fixes in the **GitHub Issues** tab, ensuring traceability and streamlining the management of the security backlog.
